      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CAPITALEX (1) didn't meet market expectation fresh when struggling to finish off after drifting back from the inside draw. Better for the hitout and can come along leaps and bounds second-up. Gets in well with the 4kg claim and is a major player this time. MR MARKLE (3) couldn't arrive in time to pay his supporters when resuming at Tatura. Was flat second-up but has been freshened and had a jump-out to get things back in order. Expecting sharp improvement. YOURAWAY (6) closed off strongly last start to finish a close second here. Interesting to see her dropping back in trip on quick back-up but she deserves consideration. SHOUT ME (4) turned in a fair effort at Horsham over 1100m at his last run five months ago, finishing fourth. Comes here with definite top-three claims fresh. RAIN LORD (5) also returns and strips fitter for two jump-outs, winning the recent. Drawn well and can be kept safe.",
